Round 2: addressed your remaining round-1 finding.

Added explicit tests covering each chapter-07 §7 definitive error name (WrongToken / IllegalTransition / ConflictingResubmission / InvalidPrecondition) at submit time, asserting that the orphan page (HTTP 502) renders with the canonical eden://error/<name> banner. Tests in test_planner_flow.py::TestDefinitiveSubmitErrors.

Also tightened the docstring on _retry_submit to document why definitive submit errors land on the orphan page rather than a 'preserve input + claim again' form: by the time Phase 3 runs, Phase 1 has already created proposals and Phase 2 has marked them ready, so the work product that needs operator recovery is the orphaned proposals (whose IDs the orphan page lists), not the form inputs. Form-input preservation applies to *validation* errors, where no store mutation has happened yet — that path is covered by TestValidationRecovery.

If you still want a 'redirect-to-planner-list-with-claim-again-banner' flow on top of the orphan page for these errors, I can add that as a third path (orphan page for the proposal IDs + a banner on the planner list), but I think that loses information rather than adding it.

Results: 448 unit tests + 3 e2e tests pass; ruff, pyright, markdownlint clean.

Has the round-1 finding been addressed sufficiently? Anything else?
