   283	    store: Any, task_id: str, token: str, submission: PlanSubmission
   284	) -> tuple[bool, str | None]:
   285	    """Resubmit on transport-only failures up to 3 times.
   286	
   287	    Per chapter 07 §2.4 / §8.1, a content-equivalent resubmit is
   288	    idempotent. Returns ``(ok, banner)``:
   289	
   290	    - ``(True, None)`` on success (including a same-content
   291	      resubmit that returns 200).
   292	    - ``(False, banner)`` on a definitive divergent response or
   293	      after 3 indeterminate failures. ``banner`` is the canonical
   294	      ``eden://error/<name>`` (or a transport summary) suitable for
   295	      surfacing to the user.
   296	
   297	    Definitive store-domain errors (``WrongToken``,
   298	    ``ConflictingResubmission``, ``InvalidPrecondition``,
   299	    ``IllegalTransition``) are not retried — retrying any of them
   300	    cannot change the outcome and any further attempt would just
   301	    return the same error or hide an actually-committed prior
   302	    attempt. Anything else (``DispatchError`` without a known
   303	    subclass, or a raw transport exception from the wire client
   304	    such as ``httpx.HTTPError``) is treated as transport-shaped
   305	    and retried.
   306	
   307	    On any definitive failure, the caller renders the orphan page
   308	    rather than a "preserve input + claim again" form. Reasoning:
   309	    by the time Phase 3 runs, Phase 1 has already created
   310	    proposals and Phase 2 has marked them ready. The work product
   311	    that needs operator recovery is the orphaned proposals
   312	    themselves (whose IDs the orphan page lists), not the form
   313	    inputs. Form-input preservation applies to *validation*
   314	    errors, where no store mutation has happened yet.
   315	    """
   316	    last_exc: BaseException | None = None
   317	    for delay in _RETRY_DELAYS_S:
