   466	5. **Phase-3 retry-before-orphan.** Per
   467	   `spec/v0/07-wire-protocol.md` §2.4 (and §8.1 on idempotency) the
   468	   resubmit semantics are defined: a content-equivalent resubmit
   469	   returns 200, a divergent resubmit returns 409
   470	   `eden://error/conflicting-resubmission`. Before declaring
   471	   proposals orphaned, the UI retries the same `submit` call up
   472	   to 3 times with exponential backoff on transport failures,
   473	   and on a clean response treats the submission as committed.
   474	   The orphaned-proposals error page is reached only after the
   475	   retries are exhausted with an indeterminate result, or the
   476	   server returns a definitive error.
   477	6. **Reclaim path on expired/invalid claim token.** If any
   478	   `store.claim` / `store.submit` returns one of the closed
   479	   wire-protocol errors —
   480	   - `eden://error/wrong-token` (presented token != stored
   481	     token; chapter 07 §7),
   482	   - `eden://error/illegal-transition` (state-machine
   483	     violation, e.g. another worker reclaimed after expiry),
   484	   - `eden://error/conflicting-resubmission` (resubmit
   485	     disagreed with committed payload),
   486	   - `eden://error/invalid-precondition` (e.g. trial state
   487	     differs from required) —
   488	   the form re-renders the planner list with a banner naming
   489	   the canonical error type and offering "claim again." Field
   490	   input is preserved across the re-render so the user does not
   491	   lose work-in-progress.
   492	7. **Errors** at any other point: re-render the form with
   493	   field-level messages; do not lose user input.
